2 Months Ago He had allegedly decided to help the Nigerian Government trace the money if he was allowed to retain $100m. According to court records, the President Muhammadu Buhari administration in 2018 confirmed its commitment to return the allotted funds to the former senator. This move has made the US and UK governments unwilling to return the stolen assets back to Nigeria. Abacha is estimated to have lodged $5bn of public funds in different foreign bank accounts during his time as Nigeria’s military dictator.